    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Many thanks for y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> kind favor of the 1<hi rend="superscript">st</hi>
                    <choice>
                        <abbr>inst.</abbr>
                        <expan>instant</expan>
                    </choice> &amp; for the agreable contents. I shall take care of <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0136">the Stirling History</title>
                    </bibl>
                    when I get to <placeName ref="pl0699">London</placeName>. about the 15<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> of next month direct to me <placeName ref="pl0787">N<hi rend="superscript">o</hi> 12 vere street oxford
                        road</placeName>; &amp; do not mind franks.</p>
                <p>I am happy to have sent you an account of <persName ref="pe0156">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Low</persName>. who wrote to me in good
                    spirits. You had my answer to his Letter last week.</p>
                <p>The <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0213">Banchorie
                        antiquities</title>
                    </bibl> are not explicit enough but I hope somebody will
                    give a fuller account &amp; also of the medals.</p>
                <p>I have kept every <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0064">magazine</title>
                    </bibl> I had of 1773. but some are wanting. I think I had
                    best have them from <persName ref="pe0260">the editor</persName> all bound; if
                    he will be so good as to take the others, which I will leave where he orders in
                        <placeName ref="pl0699">London</placeName>. I declare I lost none: but what
                    are missing were missent. I will pay any difference</p>
                <p>Is it possible to get a drawing in Indian ink of <persName ref="pe0063">cardinal
                        Beaton</persName> whose <rs type="art" ref="ar0128">portrait</rs> is in
                    Holyrood house.<note type="editorial">An engraving of Beaton's portrait appears
                        in Pennant's <bibl type="editorial">
                            <title ref="bi0010">
                                <hi rend="italic">Tour in Scotland 1772 Part II</hi>
                            </title> (London: 1776),Plate
                            XXXI., <biblScope unit="page">p.243</biblScope>.</bibl>
                    </note> I wish it
                    to be well done &amp; exactly the size of <rs type="art" ref="ar0005">my
                        admirable Crichton</rs>. So extraordinary a personage merits to be engraven.
                    &amp; it never was.</p>
                <p>I have lately seen <persName ref="pe0390">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                        Falconer</persName> who requests to be remembered to you. I am now at
                        <persName ref="pe0243">a friend’s an M.P</persName> so inclose Two cancels
                    to my <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0004 bi0008">Two
                        volumes</title>
                    </bibl>. By the pages you will soon find their places.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>I am, Dear Sir, y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> most obed<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>
                    </salute>
                    <signed>Tho. Pennant</signed>
                </closer>

                <dateline>Nov. 15<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1774.</dateline>

                <postscript>

                    <p>Pray ask some Erse critic what is <hi rend="underline">Shi an</hi> is it not
                        fairies houses. You may inclose <hi rend="underline">y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> next</hi> to <persName ref="pe0015">Sir Roger</persName>;
                        after that write to <placeName ref="pl0699">London</placeName>. I send but
                        two of the cancels this time all being over weight.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p>
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>M<hi rend="superscript">r.</hi> Paton</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Custom-house</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Edinburg—</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </p>
                <p>Free <lb/>
                    <persName ref="pe0243">PH:Yorke</persName>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <stamp type="handstamp">
                        <placeName ref="pl0002">CHESTER</placeName>
                    </stamp>
